# Cloudflare Pages — proxy /api/* to your backend
#
# HOW TO USE:
#   1. Replace BACKEND_URL below with your backend's public URL
#      - Oracle Cloud:  http://YOUR_ORACLE_IP  (or https://your-domain.com)
#      - Fly.io:        https://personal-intel-feed.fly.dev
#
#   2. Deploy your frontend/ folder to Cloudflare Pages
#      (Pages > Create project > Upload assets, or connect GitHub repo)
#
#   3. The frontend uses relative /api/* paths — Cloudflare transparently
#      proxies them to your backend via the rule below.
#
# The 200 status code means a transparent proxy (not a redirect).
# The :splat captures everything after /api/ and forwards it.

/api/*  https://YOUR_BACKEND_URL/api/:splat  200
